definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of expression of a histone-encoding gene. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript as well as any processing to produce a mature RNA product or an mRNA (for protein-coding genes) and the translation of that mRNA into protein.

label.value: positive regulation of histone gene expression

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of expression of a histone-encoding gene. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript as well as any processing to produce a mature RNA product or an mRNA (for protein-coding genes) and the translation of that mRNA into protein.

label.value: negative regulation of histone gene expression

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of expression of a histone-encoding gene. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product or products (proteins or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript as well as any processing to produce a mature RNA product or an mRNA (for protein-coding genes) and the translation of that mRNA into protein.

Catalysis of the reaction -  9beta-pimara-7,15-diene + 3 O2 + 3 NADPH + 3 H+ -eq- 9beta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-oate + 3 NADP+ + 4 H2O. This is a three-step reaction -  (a) 9beta-pimara-7,15-diene + O2 + NADPH + H+ -eq- 9beta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-ol + NADP+ + H2O, (b) 9beta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-ol + O2 + NADPH + H+ -eq- 9neta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-al + NADP+ + 2 H2O, (c) 9beta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-al + O2 + NADPH + H+ -eq- 9beta-pimara-7,15-dien-19-oate + NADP+ + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dGTP + H2O -eq- dGMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dTTP + H2O -eq- dTMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + H2O -eq- GMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ITP + H2O -eq- IMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UTP + H2O -eq- UMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  XTP + H2O -eq- xanthosine 5'-phosphate + diphosphate.

A special chromosome region located towards one end of a chromosome that contains dispersed copies of short, repetitive DNA sequences and functions as a cis-acting element essential for presynaptic homologous chromosome pairing and chromosome-nuclear envelope attachment.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an acyl-glucuronoside + H2O -eq- an alcohol + D-glucuronate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  gallate + O2 -eq- (1E)-4-oxobut-1-ene-1,2,4-tricarboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  taxusin + O2 + NADPH + H+ -eq- 7beta-hydroxytaxusin + NADP+ + H2O.
The region between the plasma membrane and the cell wall, as found in organisms such as filamentous fungi.
Catalysis of the reaction -  succinate semialdehyde + NADP+ + H2O -eq- succinate + NADPH + 2 H+.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to salt stress

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under salt stress. The stress is usually an increase or decrease in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to menadione

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a menadione stimulus. Menadione (also called vitamin K3) is a naphthoquinone having a methyl substituent at the 2-position.

The sequence of enzymatic reactions by which a cap structure is added to the 5' end of a nascent RNA polymerase II transcript. All RNA polymerase II transcripts receive a 7-methyl-G cap. Then for (at least) small nuclear RNAs (snRNAs) and small nucleolar RNAs (snoRNAs), the7-methyl-G cap is hypermethylated to become a 2,2,7-trimethylguanosine (TMG) cap.

Hypermethylation of the 7-(mono)methylguanosine (m(7)G) cap structure at the 2' position of the guanosine residue to convert a mono-methylated cap to a 2,2,7-trimethylguanosine cap structure. This type of cap modification occurs on small nuclear RNAs (snRNAs) and small nucleolar RNAs (snoRNAs) and is dependent on prior guanine-N7 methylation.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-DOPA + O2 -eq- -qm- + H2O. This reaction catalyzes the oxygenation of the dopamine precursor L-DOPA, to the corresponding o-quinone.
Catalysis of the reaction -  dopamine + O2 -eq- -qm- + H2O. This reaction catalyzes the oxygenation of dopamine to the corresponding o-quinone.
The addition of a methyl group to the N7 atom in the base portion of a guanine nucleotide residue in an RNA molecule.

A multiprotein ATPase complex involved in the release of polyubiquitinated proteins, including those damaged by oxidative stress, from the outer mitochondria membrane into the cytoplasm where they are presented to the proteasome for proteolysis, a process also referred to as mitochondria-associated degradation (MAD). In budding yeast, this complex includes Cdc48p, Npl4p and Vms1p.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to nitrogen starvation

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a deprivation of nitrogen.
Actin-based structures involved in establishing close contact between Sertoli-Sertoli cells or Sertoli-spermatids in the seminiferous tubules of the testes.
A filamentous cortical structure formed, in S. pombe, by the eisosome component Pil1.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + adenine(2030) in 23S rRNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + rRNA containing N(6)-methyladenine(2030) in 23S rRNA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + guanosine(1516) in 16S rRNA -eq- N(2)-methylguanosine(1516) in 16S rRNA + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine.
Catalysis of the ATP-dependent rewinding of single-stranded DNA (ssDNA) to reform base pairs between strands. Often acts on ssDNA bubbles bound by replication protein A (RPA).

Catalysis of the reaction -  2-(acetylamino)-4-O-[2-(acetylamino)-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl]-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose + H2O -eq- 2-(acetylamino)-4-O-(2-amino-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranosyl)-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose + acetate.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a regulatory subunit of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase. The regulatory subunit associates with the catalytic subunit to regulate both its activity and subcellular location.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the catalytic subunit of a phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase. The catalytic subunit catalyzes the addition of a phosphate group to an inositol lipid at the 3' position of the inositol ring.

label.value: SREBP-SCAP complex retention in endoplasmic reticulum

definition.value: Any process in which the SREBP-SCAP complex is maintained in the endoplasmic reticulum and prevented from moving elsewhere. The SREBP-SCAP complex is formed by the association of sterol regulatory element binding protein (SREBP) and SREBP-cleavage-activating protein (SCAP). In the absence of sterols, the SREBP-SCAP complex is packaged into COPII vesicles and travels to the Golgi apparatus to be processed. In the presence of sterols, the complex binds ER-resident proteins such as INSIG, which retain the complex in the ER.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a 5' tyrosyl-RNA phosphodiester bond between a protein and RNA. In picornaviruses, this covalent bond connects VPg, a viral-encoded protein essential for RNA replication, to the 5' end of all nascent picornavirus genomes -  it is cleaved from viral RNA prior to its engaging in protein synthesis.
Combining with a peptide pheromone, and transmitting the signal across the membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.

Combining with the mating-type peptide pheromone M-factor and transmitting the signal across the membrane to initiate a change in cell activity. M-factor is a nine-membered oligopeptide that consists of tyrosyl, threonyl, prolyl, lysyl, valyl, prolyl, tyrosyl, methionyl and methyl S-farnesylcysteinate residues joined in sequence, and is a peptide pheromone released by Schizosaccharomyces pombe cells of the cellular mating type Minus.

Combining with the mating-type peptide pheromone P-factor and transmitting the signal across the membrane to initiate a change in cell activity. P-factor is a polypeptide of 23 residues, with the sequence Thr-Tyr-Ala-Asp-Phe-Leu-Arg-Ala-Tyr-Gln-Ser-Trp-Asn-Thr-Phe-Val-Asn-Pro-Asp-Arg-Pro-Asn-Leu, and is a peptide pheromone released by Schizosaccharomyces pombe cells of the cellular mating type Plus.
Combining with vascular endothelial growth factor A (VEGF-A) and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with vascular endothelial growth factor B (VEGF-B) and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with vascular endothelial growth factor C (VEGF-C) and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with vascular endothelial growth factor D (VEGF-D) and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with vascular endothelial growth factor E (VEGF-E) and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.
Combining with placental growth factor (PlGF) and transmitting the signal across the plasma membrane to initiate a change in cell activity.
The lipid bilayer of a virion, a complete fully infectious extracellular virus particle.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-5-monosubstituted hydantoin -eq- L-5-monosubstituted hydantoin.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-desacetyl-2-hydroxyethyl bacteriochlorophyllide a -eq- bacteriochlorophyllide a + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tyrosine + S-adenosyl-L-methionine + reduced acceptor -eq- 2-iminoacetate + 4-methylphenol + 5'-deoxyadenosine + L-methionine + acceptor + 2 H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-diphosphoglycerate (DPG) + ATP -eq- cyclic 2,3-diphosphoglycerate (cDPG) + ADP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phosphoglycerate + ATP -eq- 2,3-diphosphoglycerate + ADP.
